Most dental plans share the same idea: there’s what you pay for care, when you pay for it, and how much of those care costs you and your plan share. 

That’s where terms like “copay” and “cost sharing” come in. It can all be a little confusing, so to make it easier to understand, let’s take a look at how your dental plan works.
For services other than preventive care, you pay a deductible - a set dollar amount - before your coverage kicks in.
As soon as the deducible is met, you and the plan will share the costs of services you received. Known as coinsurance, this is the percentage of costs you pay for covered dental care.

title.jcr:title: This plan pays for preventive care

text.text: Preventive and diagnostic services, including exams and cleanings, are covered 100%  when provided by a network dentist.
This plan includes a discount program where you can save on other dental services, including fillings, crowns, orthodontia and teeth whitening. The discount plan is not insurance.
There is no minimum amount that you pay before the plan begins to pay. There is also no maximum limit on how much the plan will cover each plan year.

Dreaming of a straighter, brighter smile?

Now available as part of this plan's orthodontic benefit, SmileDirectClub straightens teeth with clear aligners sent directly to you. This means you dental plan may help you get the smile you’ll love.

If you are a candidate, the dental plan may pay half the cost of your aligner treatment. Your benefit also includes these services at no extra cost:

  • A free 3D digital image at one of 235 SmileShops ($0 cost) or an at-home impression kit ($0 cost after reimbursement with rebate)
  • A free retainer following completion of your smile journey ($0 cost with subscription)
  • bright on™ premium teeth whitening ($0 cost)
  • A duly licensed dentist or orthodontist will be assigned to you to develop your treatment plan and monitor your progress

See if you are a candidate and learn more at: https://smiledirectclub.com/insurance/

Dental FlexAppeal Enhanced Program

The FlexAppeal Enhanced program is part of your UnitedHealthcare dental plan. Designed to help you keep your teeth and gums healthier healthy, this program includes three benefits:

  • Additional cleanings or gum treatments for those who have been treated for a periodontal (gum) condition. Your dentist will advise on the need for this.
  • White fillings for back teeth
  • Dental implants

Consumer MaxMultiplier rollover feature

Having the Consumer MaxMultiplier® rollover benefit allows you to earn award dollars for seeing a dentist at least once during your benefit year. If you have family members covered by your plan, each family member can earn his or her own awards.

To qualify

  1. You’ll need to visit a dentist at least once during the plan year
  2. Your dental claims must be less than an amount set by the plan.

UnitedHealthcare adds these award dollars to your annual maximum for the following year and applies them to qualifying claims. You’re able to use rollover dollars for future dental needs, except orthodontia (braces). 

NOTE: Members will not actually earn cash that they can access or withdraw.

Step-up Preventive

Our Step-up Preventive Plan design rewards you for completing preventive care. When you complete your preventive care requirements in plan year 1, you'll "step-up" to a higher coinsurance benefit in year . If you satisfy preventive care requirements in year 2, the benefit "steps up" again in plan 3. If you don't meet the requirement during the following year, the benefit will "step down" to the prior year's percentage.

If you don't meet preventive care requirements will not see a change in their benefit. The Step-up Preventive feature is designed to encourage members to take advantage of preventive care services.
